caption: By far the best fish tacos I've ever eaten

My daughter and I have been to Chiringa many times to dine in-person. The food is always excellent, and the wait has been minimal. 10-15min at most once the order has been placed.  Fair warning however, now that spring is here and Covid restrictions are apparently gone. We went this weekend to get a take-out order. It was a beautiful day and the Downtown Alpharetta area was busy. There were four parties ahead of me in line, the wait wasn't terrible to place my order - 15-min maybe. I then waited nearly an hour to get my food! And items were missing to boot, which we didn't realize until we had already arrived home.  The staff was very nice, and they credited me for the missing items. BUT, waiting an hour was ridiculous. They need to get more kitchen help or communicate the wait time.
Really love everything here. ❤
This place is absolutely the best. The staff is so nice. Ask for Aiden as your server he is amazing! The food was so good and came quickly. The best part is the live music!
Friendly service and delicious food! Got the lobster roll with plantains. YUM!!
Best fish sandwich.  Great atmosphere.
Great place to enjoy a soothing music and quick break from work. Nice work crew/fortunately the salad n drink taste is PERFECT 🤩
Awesome tacos & great vibe

We chose to eat here because it’s located in downtown Alpharetta but allows you to social distance. Food was okay, but my kids had the chicken fingers and loved them. It’s nice to be able to go somewhere where the kids can run around! Wait for food can be a little lengthy as you can only order from a window but again, conveniently allowing social distancing so worth it!!
Delicious food and drinks, great location, friendly people. Couldn't ask for more.
Super chill place with an awesome atmosphere in the middle of downtown Alpharetta.
Best fish sandwich EVER (blackened grouper), the seasoned fries were pretty good, would liked a little more thickness.
This place is just LO MEJOR in Alpharetta Downtown 🍺

This is a gluten free eater's dream! The food was amazing and the online ordering process was simple. I wish I could buy the mac and cheese buy the gallon. It's been a long time since I've had fried shrimp and it didn't disappoint. I wish I still lived close to the area. I'd eat here every week! Better yet...can we open one in Nashville??? 😁

What a delightful evening! In times of distance they are doing an excellent job of keeping everyone safe. Order from the window outside and grab a table on the patio. Or roll out a blanket on the lawn, under the stars and listen to some live music. The service is outstanding, super friendly and helpful. The food was fantastic too. I def recommend the fried plantains for a sweet and tangy starter. The grilled hot dog and fried tenders were also on point. But my favorite item was the Baja shrimp taco, fried - it's super spicy!

Well, this is the last time my family will be spending our money at Chiringa in Alpharetta. First, I’ve always thought they are extremely expensive for what you get BUT couple that with terrible service and it makes it even harder to justify the high prices. $20 for lettuce with snapper on top served in a disposable container? Crazy! In addition, the lady taking our order seemed very unhappy and got my son’s order incorrect. I heard him order and he did speak clearly but like I said, the lady taking our order seemed very unhappy about taking our order so probably wasn’t listening very well. In addition, I was literally being attacked by flies! The flies weren’t just trying to get to my food, they were actually landing on me! So, that was annoying too! Nobody checking on people at the tables to see if they need anything. With lots of other restaurants nearby and during a pandemic, Chiringa really needs to step it up and offer better service and more for their customer’s money!
I love their location and drinks were really good and strong. I haven't tried their food though.
Loved it my girlfriend is a veggie lol they had options for her shrimp basket was amazing Mac n cheese on steroids we will be back.
Best Baja Fish Tacos Anywhere!
Great cocktails! Yummy Frose! My only complaint is the patrons surrounding it really don’t believe in wearing masks or social distancing, but you can grab a to-go drink and keep on walking!
The food at this place is phenomenal & the staff was so friendly! I really enjoyed my experience here. Being a Florida native, I appreciated the ambience & food.

We have been to Chiringa over a dozen times.  The food is outstanding and we usually find something new to try.  The drinks are amazing and we always get generous pours.  To top it off, the staff projects a positive attitude and great energy.  It is always a treat to go to Chiringa!!
Food was surprisingly good. Used fresh ingredients for sure. Had impression that they well take care of covid concerns. Safe spot for sure.
Great place to hangout.  Tacos are great and the stuff is really friendly.

They do not use bib lettuce ...so it's a poor substitute whatever they use looked like baby romaine.  The menu made them sound flavorful but there was not much flavor to our chicken and shrimp tacos. Will not be ordering them again.   Less than friendly service
This place is amazing! The staff is great.

Oh my gosh the best so chique ,cool bar restaurant kinda feel, reminds you of a beach setting they have menu items that are way better than the normal around here sick of same fast food blues! You’ve gotten get the bowl and the plantain margaritas are off the hook! A friendly staff and they always take care no fake customer service cool people. Give them a shot if your in this  area . Other major cities could use this type vibe!

Staff was nice, but the wait was super long. My husband ordered after me from Smoke Jacks across the street and received his food and finished eating before my order was ready. The tacos were great, chips were delicious, but the Pico was terrible. Canned tomatoes mixed with a few onions and peppers. Not sure if they couldn’t find fresh tomatoes??

We had an amazing experience with Chiringa. Due to social distancing, we ordered our food to go and we had a very large order. My group also ordered two gallons of their OG frozen margarita that was absolutely delicious! And while we were waiting for our food, the wonderful staff brought us complimentary shots. I cannot wait to come back!
Great food and atmosphere!
Really liked the bowl I got..plenty of gluten free, vegan, vegetarian cases

I LOVE this place! I have multiple food allergies. Lots of gluten free options. What an amazing find! The place is so cheerful, the people are nice, and the food is yummy! They have great fresh salads and sauces. I can actually get breaded chicken fingers and fries without having to worry about it. They have dedicated fryers. Even if you don’t have allergies, this place is GREAT!
Fresh, delicious, simple but tasty
The Jerk Chicken is the BEST I have had in a looooong time.
Best Margaritas I've ever had. This is not an exaggeration. I'm also a fan of their bowls. My wife always gets the Chop chop bowl. My favorite is the Power 57.
Service and Mahi sandwich we're both amazing. Will definitely be back!
Their fish tacos could really taste a lot better for the price

Shrimp tacos and cocktail were very good, everything else was mediocre and overpriced, especially for counter service. More specifically, the rice was microwave rice and very salty, and the guacamole tasted funny (may have been mixed with sour cream or something), and the chicken tacos were dry. I'd come back but I'd only order the shrimp tacos.
Kinda Expensive, service was good, good wasn't great, I'm not sure I would go back, a burger and chicken strips two sodas $ 40.00 bucks.
Excellent margaritas!!
They have great margaritas!!
The best margaritas ever!

We LOVE chiringa! Great fresh fish tacos, really delicious guacamole served with equally delicious tortilla and plantain chips. Oh... and you can’t come here unless you get a cocktail in a bucket, which pack a punch, but an enjoyable one.
Attentive staff but Overpriced food of poor quality. The “fresh” fish tacos smelled I had to return. Good drinks though.
The fries are the best thing there.
Great healthy options and friendly staff. Good portion size, and very very fresh. Would eat here again for sure.
Best place to grab strong drinks and fresh fiah

Had the Baja tacos with grilled shrimp here. The ingredients were cooked to order and were DELICIOUS. Also the plantains are fantastic, if you’re a fan of fried Maduros then make your way here. The corn tortilla is subtle so it does not overpower the contents and they don’t overfill the tacos so you can actually eat them with your hand! The cilantro sauce and lemon aioli are also fire.
Good beer, nice atmosphere. Good too salty.

Fun atmosphere and music in downtown Alpharetta BUT it took over an hour to get our food (3 burgers and 1 kids chicken fingers). The burgers were flat and well done which was  disappointing.  The plantains were great and the chicken was average. Overall, I would not go back here as no one came over to explain the wait and I had to go up for information twice. Not awesome when you have kids with you where are hungry!

"Elevated beach food..." Went for lunch with a coworker. Order fish tacos (grouper) and a side of fries for $21+. It was tasty and fresh but I'm not sure it was worth the price. I guess I was paying for eating on the square.
Food was flavorful and the hospitality was top notch. Even the quinoa was good ;-)

Me and my gf came to eat this morning. We had a payment issue/error at the counter which once the owner or manager realized we encountered, he came over and bought our whole lunch. He said that’s not a good way to start a Friday. Food was great! Nice to have someone go out there way to ensure a happy experience/ payed attention to the situation. Will be back for the tacos again.

Horrible! Never will be back again. The set up is a rip off. The attendants have to charge, make the drinks, take the food order, and a line waiting to be waited. It is a Mafia the business is making a lot of money while the costumers are waiting on line forever and the employees are killing themselves to please the customers. The food is terrible full of sodium and taste like it is spoiled.
Awesome location, great food and service! Thanks Travis for hosting the Atlanta Pitt Club!
Staff is SO nice, place is super clean and the service is awesome!!! 10/10 recommended!
Overall its a nice place but fish tacos were way too expensive for what is served

On a hot summer day, it's hard to not just get some chips and guac and a tall beer from here when you're downtown. It's a Meetup spot Among friends before we go for dinner. Delicious food and low prices on amazing beers. Can't really be beat to start your night on the town here.
Awesome venue with excellent food and vibe!
We ate it all! And the best part staff was great! Manager Andy is a great leader! Keep up the amazing atmosphere and excellent food!
We had fun
Fun
Drinks were on point, fish tacos were yummy, bowl was good get the curry sauce on the side.we will be back!
Stopped in for a snack and cocktail.   I was disappointed that they were out of guacamole and pico de gallo.  The hummus was good though.

Don’t get the bowl...the rice might break your teeth. Manager told us the reason for the lemonade being so unenjoyable was to “compete with chic Fil a.” At best the food is mediocre and customer service is not a priority.
Just had drinks, which were good and the staff was nice
Never ate or drank here before but I did used their bathroom once. Super clean 5 star bathroom for sure
It was a lively environment with attentive customer service...really enjoyed the GF fish tacos and the plantain chips.
Cold drinks and always kid friendly
Awesome bowls and healthy food. Decor is nice and great atmosphere!
Enjoyed our visit; simple and yummy food, fast service and ringa rita was 👍
Fried Plantains and the Fish Tacos were awesome. They have some nice summer cocktails as well.

TERRIBLE customer service...by the OWNER! Not even going to comment about the mediocre food. My mom left her credit card here and called after leaving. The employee she spoke to confirmed her card was there and put in the safe. When she arrived to pick it up a couple days later no one could seem to find it. The employees confirmed the had “seen it around” but no one found it. She came back the next day at opening when all the staff and owner were present. The owner said it wasn’t his problem and that she should know how to order a new card. They also claimed that one employee cut up the card. It’s an indestructible Chase Visa so that didn’t add up either. Bottom line the we’re incredibly rude and someone threw her card away.
After 3rd visit I can confidently give this place 5 solid stars. Great food, great atmosphere, friendly staff, prime location. Couldn't ask for more.

We really wanted it to be great. The atmosphere was fun and beachy. The menu looked good, but the wait time for food was over 30 mins after ordering on a weekday afternoon, and then the fries were soggy and tasted like old fryer oil, like it needed to be changed. My power bowl would have been great, but the rice was under cooked and crunchy to where it hurt my teeth. I didn't complain becuase I knew it would take forever to resolve. The worst was that we ordered the plantains and guac which looked amazing, but my son said he started feeling bad after eating it, (didn't tell me until we got in the car) and by the time we were almost home, 25 mins drive we both had to race to the bathroom from bad stomach cramps and super upset stomach. I think we got some sort of food poisoning and the plantains and guac were the only thing we both ate. It was awful, we felt terrible for the rest of the day and a day after.
IT WAS HORRIFIC IT WAS DRY BLAND AND FROZEN FOOD!!
Worst food experience, overcooked and looking old food! Who does pico de gallo and guacamole with a dice tomatoes can?
Horrible!!! Chicken fingers and fries were over cooked and look like yesterday food. Guacamole done with dice tomatoes from a can as well as the pico de gallo. I will never go back again.

A little overpriced for the portions and quality of food, but overall good enough to go back. They messed up my order a little despite being dead slow, but were otherwise good. I enjoyed the outdoor seating and the homemade (and very tart) lemonade.
Very disappointing. Ordered the fish tacos at the “ Market” price. Turned out they were $19! For two fish tacos. Ridiculous price for average tacos at best. Will not be going back.
OMG, I had the taco shrimp and it was lovely. Try to get the green Aoili sauce. YUMMY!
Good seafood with a great location.
Careless in making drinks
Good food,service and ambience.
Food and drinks were excellent! Nice atmosphere as well.

Great food and relaxed vibe.  Welcoming and friendly folks.  Orders are made to order, so even though it's counter service for your order, it's not Fast.  But not horribly long either.  Decent lunch crowd there on a light rain and cooler Sunday in June, and the weather may have helped with table availability.  Had the Braves on one TV, and the women's world soccer match on the other.  Hubby had a bowl which he said was very good.  I had the fish taco (catch of the day was mahi, and opted for blackened.). Yummmm.  Their fries are thin and crispy, the way I like them.
New building in the middle of downtown Alpharetta.  Small but very cozy

This is a newly opened restaurant in the heart of Alpharetta downtown. It's beach themed and they did a great job with the decor. If you don't look outside it feels like one of those beach shack restaurants in Clearwater, Florida.  Food: this was the best part of the restaurant. I heard this was owned by the same people who did Tin Lizzy's so I was skeptical of the food quality but they knocked it out of the park. I had a fish sandwich costing $16 that was comparable to a $30 fish entree you would purchase at a nice sit down restaurant. My wife had one of there bowls costing $11 and she felt it was remarkable. The food is very healthy, tastes great, and was cooked to perfection.  Drinks: they have your typical beers and wines in addition to frozen Rose and margaritas. The drinks we're tasty but cocktails were a bit overpriced in my honest opinion. $4 beer. $11 margarita.  Seating: this place is kinda small with typical high top and booth tables inside. There are only about 10 or less indoors. The outdoor seating is great though. They have about 4 picnic tables with adjustable umbrellas for shade. They also have some Adirondack chairs perched under some beautiful trees.  Parking: none specific to the restaurant but Alpharetta downtown has ample parking within a few blocks of the town square. For now at least.
Good food and beverages (Chiringa 'Rita). Portions are a bit short of premium price when compared to other venues at this location.

Great location, terrific staff. Could use a touch of variety on the taco choices. @chiringa go check out @taqueriadelsol and take a couple of easy ideas to incorporate. Perfect spot for a beachy bite and enjoying downtown Alpharetta!

Love this place. Feels like you're at the beach while you're there. Food is fantastic.  Margaritas are delicious. It's Alpharetta, so you'll pay a little more than the average Mexican/Tex Mex, but it's worth it.
Food portions are pretty small for the price. Food is ok.
Great beach shack ambience. Good is okay
Great service, food and drinks!! Beautiful location as well.  We had a great time!

It was a pleasant experience in a busy but quaint center of town of Alpharetta. I loved the atmosphere. The menu fits the name where they serve a nice handful of food items and plentiful variety of drinks. This restaurant has outdoor seating and a nice grassy area for the kids to run around.  I would definitely go back to Chiringa.
Fun place to eat and relax.  Great drinks and food served by an awesome staff!
The food is delicious. Great atmosphere, extraordinary service. We were well taken care of.
Delicious food and awesome drinks. They are only missing a nice dessert.

I love chiringa! The atmosphere is always great, and the team members Lauren and Ryan are always in a great mood and they really make a solid marg. The outdoor space is enormous and can shift around. A true beach vibe!
Very expensive. Took forever for food to come out. Place is in really cool spot. Great walk in walk out beer service.
Hands down best margaritas in Alpharetta.   The food is good and the vibe is outstanding.  Very family and dog friendly.
Very fun atmosphere.  Stop by for a signature cocktail.  Great outdoor and indoor space as well.  Cornhole games and big screen T.V.'s.  Great place to go and hang out!
Great food and even better Service. Easy to get to as it's in the heart of the new downtown Alpharetta. My go to lunch spot!

So far so good! We went for the first time and it was so busy but the staff was super attentive. The plantain chips with Guacamole was delicious. The wines are really good by the glass. The atmosphere is fun and can't wait to try other things on the menu!
Such a great beach vibe and terrific assortment of food. The staff is exceptionally friendly. The drinks are refreshing and the hummus is my favorite.

The wait at 2 o'clock on Saturday afternoon was beyond painfully slow... I waited in line for 45 minutes even though there were only 8 people in front of me. Then we waited 45 more minutes to get our food. However the atmosphere is amazing, people are super friendly and the food was absolutely incredible! I'll be going back. Hoping there was a random reason for the wait and that it's not the norm.
IT GOES IN
Great food (shrimp tacos) and drinks! Highly recommend the margarita!!! Great location, atmosphere and decor.  Owner made sure we were well taken care of.
Good atmosphere decent food
Food was good, service could have been much better.

Awesome casual spot in town.  You can grab and go or eat there - the service was great.  Our table enjoyed everything from the burger and fries to the tacos and salads.  And omg, try one of their Smiley Face cookies to finish - so fun!

I'm very impressed with how much downtown Alpharetta has improved over the past few years. Chiringa fits right in with an added Beach theme which is nice this far from the beach. Menu for lunch is pretty limited but enough variety where everyone in your group should be able to find something they like. I had the fish sandwich which was very good however I'm still suffering from sticker shock. They do it via market price. Today was fresh snapper. Awesome in theory but $17 for a small piece of fish.. ouch. $21 for lunch after tax and tip with water to drink. I would have to suggest they find a piece of fish for a normal price fish sandwich and then also offer an upgraded fresh option. Just my two cents. Loved the place other than that. Nice addition to Alpharetta.
Have really great food and drinks and the people are so nice

The best fish sandwich I've ever had. The homemade chips were fantastic.  The frozen margarita hit the spot. My husband thought his chicken sandwich was dry and a bit rubbery to chew. It's too bad because the fish and paella rice was superb! Great lunch spot!

The atmosphere there is great, not a big restaurant but fun and casual with outdoor seating. One page menu, drinks are available. The homemade chips were delicious. My wife thoroughly enjoyed her Red Snapper sandwich, however, my fried chicken sandwich was one of the worst I have ever had, thin and completely dried out. I hope for them it was just a one-time bad serving. Without having a server I didn't feel like trying to order a replacement.

Great time at Chiringa!!! Our first visit...Went with a party of 6 & hung out for 3+ hours! Delicious food & good portion sizes! Our table LOVED the guacamole, pico, & house made chips...YUM!!! The staff was welcoming & responsive! The atmosphere is fun to boot! Go check them out!
Margaritas are on point for day drinking

Great location to get a quick bite and let the kids play in the lawn. Fun atmosphere and plenty of parking. The menu is limited and the drinks are priced a little high but it is a good family lunch spot.
Good people and nice little hideaway tucked right off the main street in alpharetta

Stopped by for a quick bite for lunch and had a great time. We had a couple of beers, some chips and guac and chicken fingers. The place is really nice and staff super friendly. A great spot on a beautiful day. Dog friendly also. We will be back
Not much flavor. Chicken tacos was not worth the price.

This is a really cool place and a nice addition to City Center. The food is fresh and delicious. I've been several times but have only had food twice. I loved the grouper sandwich ($20) absolutely delicious. I've also had the fish tacos and a side salad ($22 total and that was with water - no alcohol). I think it is a bit pricey for walk-up counter service but the food and drinks were awesome and the service is great so it's still 5 stars from me. Looking forward to warmer weather and hanging out on the green with these guys!

Loved it. Great vibe. Great food. Great drinks. Had the hummus and a bowl, with blackened shrimp and garlic aioli. My wife really loved the in-house chips...get something with chips. Had the Rita and Island Lemonade. Both were great, good amount of liquor in each. The lemonade was the hit though. If you like pineapple, which we both do, get that and you'll thank me. Bar tender/waiter Watt was great. Nice guy. Sorry, no photos, were too busy enjoying.

Amazing and Fun atmosphere! I came her for dinner with my Mom and it was amazing! The staff was very friendly and fu. To chat with. I had the bowl with grilled fish of the day and Mom had the blackened fish tacos! The food was fresh and had great flavor and seasoned well! But the show stopper had to be the MARGARITAS!! Definitely will be back aging and will bring friends!
Great beach comfort food, awesome atmosphere, and outstanding service! We'll definitely be coming back, it's a great place to enjoy nice weather.

GREAT RESTAURANT!  My sister and I went there two nights ago and had a terrific time!  The food was fresh and delicious, the drinks were outstanding (I had the amazing cucumber cocktail!), and the atmosphere was fun!  The staff treated us nicely, and we will definitely go back! Thumbs up, Travis!  Thank you!

It was a more relaxed atmosphere than I expected,  but the beachy theme was a much needed break from the winter cold.  It's a fast casual restaurant,  but we had a waiter check in on us several times. We ordered a BloodyMary, Cucumber Fresher, and vodka soda, all of them were delicious and strong.  Our entrees were good, but the real stars were the sauces.  After our meal we ordered an extra order of the curry sauce and green goddess dressing to go.

Delicious foods + well poured tasty drinks + excellent customer service and attention to detail = unbeatable spot! We all had such a good time in such rainy ugly day! The place made everything that much better! Glad we stopped in, will certainly be stopping by often! 🔸Totally would recommend this place!🔸Healthy options as well! 🔸Sauces are delicious!
Service was great. Fish sandwich and fish tacos are the way to go. Will be back for more.
This place is amazing!!! Super friendly staff and excellent food!  Awesome customer service. You need to check it out!!!
Awesome fish

LOVE THIS PLACE! My sister and I came for lunch and ended up coming back for dinner the same day so we could share this new local treasure with our parents. Andy, Watts, and their team have put together an amazing restaurant. The atmosphere is so welcoming and is designed to bring back those warm fuzzy memories of your favorite vacation. All their protein is fresh and never frozen so they may run out on occasion which is just fine with me, knowing everything is fresh makes the experience that much better.  A couple highlights -highly recommend the chop chop bowl (their paella rice is incredible)! -music playlist is incredible -great location to enjoy a sunny afternoon or an easy evening
Just moved to the area and walked over to check out the food.  Was told the kitchen is closed even though the restaurant doesn't close for another hour! WTH? They ran out of food?? #poorplanning

Amazing new concept! Great food! Try the plantains (they are AWESOME) and their signature margarita..service is exceptional! Great addition to Alpharetta! The General Manager, Watts, checked our table several times to ensure everything was great! We will definitely be back! :)

Mediterranean salad and chop chop salad were great. Margarita and Mimosa were great even though the mimosa isn't on the menu. Staff is great and friendly, and it's clean and family friendly. Food is fresh, and its in a great location. Service was great!!
Neat decor, great food and service.
Great food and great service. People were so friendly and we really enjoyed the atmosphere. Drinks were amazing and we will definitely come back!!

Excellent food, staff, and atmosphere! I got the blackened Mahi tacos with fries and a frozen margarita. I happened to be in the area on a Friday night and stopped in for something new. The service was top notch and Andy answered all of my questions and made recommendations. Definitely coming back and telling friends. Perfect addition to downtown Alpharetta.
The Chop Chop bowl was great.  Love the curry chicken.   It was fresh and filling.  24 oz draft hit the spot.
This new place is awesome! We’ve been 3 times already. The food is delicious, the people are nice and the margaritas are legit! Definitely our new favorite spot in Alpharetta...
Great food!
